00:55:04,570 --> 00:55:07,761
- I think I lost my job.
- Really?

931
00:55:08,811 --> 00:55:10,061
Yeah.

932
00:55:14,670 --> 00:55:16,643
Tha--that's all the milk
you're gonna use?

933
00:55:16,743 --> 00:55:19,792
Absolutely.
This time I got it beat.

934
00:55:20,735 --> 00:55:22,944
So, uh, what's the deal
with your job?

935
00:55:23,688 --> 00:55:26,759
Melanie came over
for my new book.

936
00:55:27,731 --> 00:55:31,251
- And I kinda told her off.
- Ho ho! Head honcho, huh?

937
00:55:31,351 --> 00:55:33,838
Uh, you "kinda" told her off?
What exactly does that mean?

938
00:55:34,982 --> 00:55:38,417
I told her, the only reason
she has a job,

939
00:55:38,517 --> 00:55:40,873
was because she
slept with the boss.

940
00:55:42,514 --> 00:55:43,797
Oh, man!

941
00:55:44,155 --> 00:55:46,424
Do you think this'll affect
my Christmas bonus?

942
00:55:46,524 --> 00:55:48,384
Well, at least you
went out with a flare.

943
00:55:48,484 --> 00:55:51,207
Yeah. I don't know
what I'm gonna do about money.

944
00:55:51,307 --> 00:55:54,516
Hey, 10 years, this isn't
even gonna matter.

945
00:55:55,213 --> 00:55:57,840
You gotta relax.
You're too tense.

946
00:55:57,940 --> 00:55:59,383
No, I'm not.

947
00:56:00,323 --> 00:56:02,849
- Look at your foot.
- What?

948
00:56:03,772 --> 00:56:07,338
I just do that so...
bugs won't get on it.

949
00:56:08,403 --> 00:56:10,634
I... uh--I'll bet you five bucks

950
00:56:10,734 --> 00:56:13,161
you can't stop shakin' your foot
for five minutes straight.

951
00:56:14,168 --> 00:56:16,328
- You're tossing your money away.
- Five?

952
00:56:16,428 --> 00:56:17,727
- Ten!
- Fifteen?

953
00:56:17,827 --> 00:56:19,463
- Fifteen!
- Okay.

954
00:56:19,563 --> 00:56:20,774
Okay.

955
00:56:21,484 --> 00:56:23,050
You're gonna have to
stop it first.

956
00:56:23,909 --> 00:56:25,233
No problem.

957
00:56:26,843 --> 00:56:29,217
- Okay, ready?
- Yeah.

958
00:56:29,317 --> 00:56:30,547
Go!

959
00:56:41,823 --> 00:56:44,007
I had a rough day.
I'm keyed up.

960
00:56:44,107 --> 00:56:45,275
I don't want your money.

961
00:56:45,375 --> 00:56:46,654
- Take it.
- No.

962
00:56:46,754 --> 00:56:47,776
- Take it!
- I don't want it!

963
00:56:47,876 --> 00:56:49,413
Look, you won the bet.
Don't piss me off.

964
00:56:49,513 --> 00:56:51,718
- Take the money!
- Okay, okay, okay.

965
00:56:51,818 --> 00:56:54,702
I tell you what, I tell you what...
I'll pay you fifteen bucks,

966
00:56:54,802 --> 00:56:57,051
if you tell me another thing
you said to Melanie.

967
00:56:57,930 --> 00:57:02,643
I told her to take Happy the Clam
and shove him up her butt.

968
00:57:03,814 --> 00:57:06,970
Oh, yeah!
You're d--oh, man!

969
00:57:07,070 --> 00:57:08,844
I wish I could have seen that.

970
00:57:10,191 --> 00:57:13,954
- My life sucks!
- Oh, life doesn't suck.

971
00:57:14,054 --> 00:57:16,121
You just have to
have the right outlook.

972
00:57:16,221 --> 00:57:18,270
We're all here
to serve a purpose, okay?

973
00:57:18,370 --> 00:57:20,635
To be as good and helpful
as we can, and, uh...

974
00:57:20,735 --> 00:57:22,714
Later on we die,
and find out how we did.

975
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:23,897
In the tunnel?

976
00:57:23,997 --> 00:57:25,380
- What?
- You know, the tunnel?

977
00:57:25,480 --> 00:57:28,060
Everyone that's been clinically dead
says they were in a tunnel,

978
00:57:28,160 --> 00:57:29,799
with a bright light
in the end.

979
00:57:29,899 --> 00:57:32,053
Could you even imagine?
We die,

980
00:57:32,153 --> 00:57:34,265
and we go someplace
worse than this?

981
00:57:34,365 --> 00:57:37,285
A tunnel?
Dark tunnel, bright light...

982
00:57:37,385 --> 00:57:40,236
Tell me there isn't gonna be, like,
tons of moths all over the place.

983
00:57:40,618 --> 00:57:43,044
All right, the light
is probably God.

984
00:57:43,564 --> 00:57:46,188
- Oh, here we go.
- You still don't believe in God?

985
00:57:46,288 --> 00:57:49,804
No, I definitely believe in God.
He's the guy that needs all the money.

986
00:57:50,084 --> 00:57:51,862
- Definitely believe in him.
- Okay, no...

987
00:57:51,962 --> 00:57:55,491
God is, uh... God is peace.
Thane, everybody needs God.

988
00:57:57,964 --> 00:57:59,164
Okay.

989
00:58:00,292 --> 00:58:03,875
Then how do you explain
all the starving people in the world?

990
00:58:03,975 --> 00:58:08,469
Hmm? I mean what about
cruelty and murder?

991
00:58:08,569 --> 00:58:10,670
What about rape?
What about war?

992
00:58:10,770 --> 00:58:13,433
Okay, yeah, sure, absolutely.
There's a lot of pain in the world.

993
00:58:13,533 --> 00:58:17,788
It i--it isn't God's will.
Man has a free will.

994
00:58:17,888 --> 00:58:20,674
W-we were given the ability
to be good and helpful,

995
00:58:20,774 --> 00:58:22,967
or the ability to steal
or kill or be cruel.

996
00:58:23,067 --> 00:58:24,294
It's--it's our decision.

997
00:58:24,394 --> 00:58:27,538
And everytime we make a bad decision,
somebody else suffers.

998
00:58:27,638 --> 00:58:29,936
Like, uh... uh... Somebody's
walking down the street

999
00:58:30,036 --> 00:58:31,683
and belts you in the head
with a hammer.

1000
00:58:32,005 --> 00:58:33,861
You're gonna suffer
because of his decision.

1001
00:58:33,961 --> 00:58:36,548
We're all dependent on
one another for happiness.

1002
00:58:37,235 --> 00:58:40,820
God doesn't cause that stuff, Thane.
It's the wrong decisions of man.

1003
00:58:41,196 --> 00:58:43,156
Then man sucks.

1004
00:58:43,555 --> 00:58:46,705
Does it always have to
come down to something sucking?

1005
00:58:50,131 --> 00:58:51,842
I think it does.

1006
00:58:56,582 --> 00:58:59,158
- It's just a fly.
- Everything basically sucks.

1007
00:58:59,258 --> 00:59:02,034
I know it.
I can feel it inside of me.

1008
00:59:02,134 --> 00:59:04,470
I agree with you;
man is basically evil.

1009
00:59:04,570 --> 00:59:05,690
- And that's why everything sucks.
- Wait a minute.

1010
00:59:05,790 --> 00:59:08,019
- Man isn't basically evil.
- You said it yourself.

1011
00:59:08,119 --> 00:59:10,125
You said it. Things are
screwed up because of man.

1012
00:59:10,225 --> 00:59:12,841
No, no, no, no.
I didn't--no, man's bad decisions,

1013
00:59:12,941 --> 00:59:14,969
that's not being evil.
Ok--look, we make mistakes.

1014
00:59:15,069 --> 00:59:17,822
Often times we regret these mistakes.
That's not being evil.

1015
00:59:17,922 --> 00:59:21,019
People are evil and sadistic.
Every single one.

1016
00:59:21,119 --> 00:59:22,640
- Wait a second!
- I can prove it, I can prove it!

1017
00:59:22,740 --> 00:59:25,030
Have you ever picked up
a little puppy and held it?

1018
00:59:25,143 --> 00:59:26,267
Yeah.

1019
00:59:26,367 --> 00:59:27,938
Okay, well, you know
how cute they are?

1020
00:59:28,502 --> 00:59:29,766
- Yeah.
- Okay.

1021
00:59:29,866 --> 00:59:31,697
So you've been holding the puppy,
and it's so cute.

1022
00:59:31,797 --> 00:59:34,210
For that one little second in time,
you really love him,

1023
00:59:34,310 --> 00:59:36,037
and you give him a squeeze,

1024
00:59:36,137 --> 00:59:39,095
but he's so cute, you just
wanna squeeze him a little harder.

1025
00:59:39,955 --> 00:59:41,430
- Yeah?
- Well, there you go.

1026
00:59:41,530 --> 00:59:44,548
There's a direct tie-in between
love and wanting to kill something.

1027
00:59:44,834 --> 00:59:46,429
Oh, come on!
Wait a second!

1028
00:59:46,529 --> 00:59:47,777
No, it's true, it's true.
You squeeze it,

1029
00:59:47,877 --> 00:59:49,609
and you just wanna
squeeze it a little harder,

1030
00:59:49,709 --> 00:59:51,744
you know, it's just like:
"Oh, you're so cute."

1031
00:59:51,844 --> 00:59:53,519
"I just wanna squeeze you."

1032
00:59:53,619 --> 00:59:57,291
"I just wanna squeeze you.
I just wanna squeeze you!"

1033
00:59:57,391 --> 00:59:59,839
"There!
That's how cute you are!"

1034
01:00:00,256 --> 01:00:03,340
You gotta admit.
You've experienced that emotion.

1035
01:00:03,440 --> 01:00:05,182
Look, look, no.
Come o--no.

1036
01:00:05,282 --> 01:00:07,164
Even if that thought
of squeezing something hard

1037
01:00:07,264 --> 01:00:09,161
enters people's minds,
they don't actually do it.

1038
01:00:09,261 --> 01:00:10,715
'Cause they know
they would hurt the thing.

1039
01:00:10,815 --> 01:00:12,303
They--they, uh, stop squeezing,

1040
01:00:12,403 --> 01:00:14,963
because they don't want anything
bad or painful to happen.

1041
01:00:15,063 --> 01:00:18,531
You're just showing affection, and
you get carried away with emotion.

1042
01:00:18,631 --> 01:00:21,574
I don't believe it!
There's no way!

1043
01:00:21,674 --> 01:00:25,114
It's like it defies
all logic and reason!

1044
01:00:25,214 --> 01:00:27,606
- What?
- The cereal!

1045
01:00:28,716 --> 01:00:30,518
It's a long story.

1046
01:00:34,693 --> 01:00:38,971
Now what the hell
do you suppose that was?

1047
01:00:39,508 --> 01:00:42,050
- I don't know.
- It's unbelievable.

1048
01:00:42,150 --> 01:00:45,040
He's either constantly
blaring wretched music,

1049
01:00:45,140 --> 01:00:48,776
or he's, like, training for
some shot put competition.

1050
01:00:48,876 --> 01:00:51,035
- It's unbearable!
- What's eating you, man?

1051
01:00:51,135 --> 01:00:52,431
It's sometihng else.

1052
01:00:56,167 --> 01:00:57,345
Have...

1053
01:00:57,445 --> 01:00:59,867
Have you been playing some kind
of joke on me lately?

1054
01:01:00,588 --> 01:01:01,969
What are you--

1055
01:01:02,069 --> 01:01:04,063
- You found out.
- It was you!

1056
01:01:04,163 --> 01:01:06,835
- How did you find out?
- Of course it was you!

1057
01:01:06,935 --> 01:01:08,662
Who else would go
to all that trouble?

1058
01:01:08,762 --> 01:01:11,075
Man! I gotta admit,
you had me going!

1059
01:01:11,175 --> 01:01:12,967
It wasn't that--that much trouble.

1060
01:01:13,067 --> 01:01:14,110
- Not that much trouble?
- Yeah.

1061
01:01:14,210 --> 01:01:16,806
But you had to
make the first phone call.

1062
01:01:16,906 --> 01:01:18,619
Slip that little piece
of paper in with my mail,

1063
01:01:18,719 --> 01:01:20,901
after the mailman came,
but before I could get it.

1064
01:01:21,001 --> 01:01:23,034
Interrupting the phone call
from my mom.

1065
01:01:23,134 --> 01:01:24,695
I don't even know how you
set up that long thing

1066
01:01:24,795 --> 01:01:28,118
with the carpet cleaner survey.
How'd you make that voice?

1067
01:01:28,218 --> 01:01:29,523
What are you talking about?

1068
01:01:29,949 --> 01:01:33,391
- All that stuff. 8 o'clock.
- What happens at 8 o'clock?

1069
01:01:33,491 --> 01:01:35,467
Hey, don't mess around.
You allready told me it was you.

1070
01:01:35,567 --> 01:01:37,539
I-I, uh... I thought you were
talking about your car.

1071
01:01:37,639 --> 01:01:39,084
- My car?
- Yeah.

1072
01:01:39,184 --> 01:01:41,570
I--you know, I've been writing
"wash me" in all the windows.

1073
01:01:41,810 --> 01:01:43,460
- That was you?
- Yeah.

1074
01:01:43,560 --> 01:01:45,000
You bastard!
Why would you--

1075
01:01:45,100 --> 01:01:47,053
Wait, wait, wait, wha--what,
what's this, uh... what, uh...

1076
01:01:47,153 --> 01:01:50,242
Somebody's going to
clean your carpets at 8 o'clock?

1077
01:01:52,383 --> 01:01:55,659
- Are you playing around?
- No, I swear!

1078
01:02:02,170 --> 01:02:03,851
Hey!
What's the deal, Al?

1079
01:02:03,951 --> 01:02:05,247
Are you okay?

1080
01:02:08,565 --> 01:02:10,203
I think I'm going crazy.

1081
01:02:11,829 --> 01:02:13,754
I keep seeing stuff, too.

1082
01:02:13,854 --> 01:02:15,695
I tell you,
you gotta relax, man.

1083
01:02:15,795 --> 01:02:17,369
Get away.
Take a vacation.

1084
01:02:17,469 --> 01:02:19,063
Please.
I hate vacations.

1085
01:02:19,163 --> 01:02:21,078
Even if you have a good time,
the second you get back,

1086
01:02:21,178 --> 01:02:22,338
everybody bugs you.

1087
01:02:22,438 --> 01:02:24,265
"Oh, dude, did you
have a good time?

1088
01:02:24,365 --> 01:02:26,187
"What'd you do?
Did you bring any pictures?"

1089
01:02:26,287 --> 01:02:27,634
It's a nightmare!

1090
01:02:27,734 --> 01:02:30,188
Couldn't be doing that bad.
You're still complaining about everything.

1091
01:02:30,976 --> 01:02:32,676
Um, look, I wanna hear
about this stuff.

1092
01:02:32,776 --> 01:02:34,102
I really do.
I gotta get back to work.

1093
01:02:34,202 --> 01:02:35,489
I'll come right back, though.

1094
01:02:35,589 --> 01:02:36,974
I'll come right back.
We'll grab a bite.

1095
01:02:37,074 --> 01:02:38,828
- You can fill me in, okay?
- No restaurants.

1096
01:02:38,928 --> 01:02:40,533
No, no.
No restaurants.

1097
01:02:41,132 --> 01:02:43,960
- What time do you get off?
- I'll be done about 8:30.

1098
01:02:44,060 --> 01:02:46,412
- That's too late.
- What do you mean?

1099
01:02:48,232 --> 01:02:50,794
I don't know.
Go to work.

1100
01:02:50,894 --> 01:02:53,518
- You gotta go to work.
- Yeah, I gotta get back. Um...

1101
01:02:53,618 --> 01:02:54,773
All right...

1102
01:02:55,265 --> 01:02:57,825
I'll knock off early, okay?
I'll be here 8:15.

1103
01:02:57,925 --> 01:03:00,921
8:30 the latest, okay?
A-and you gotta promise me something.

1104
01:03:01,021 --> 01:03:03,282
That you're not gonna sit
around here in the dark all day,

1105
01:03:03,382 --> 01:03:05,780
thinkin' about crummy stuff,
gettin' all depressed, okay?

1106
01:03:06,758 --> 01:03:09,230
- Promise.
- Promise.

1107
01:03:10,255 --> 01:03:12,726
Okay.
I'll see you later.

1108
01:03:23,493 --> 01:03:24,960
Vietnam.

1109
01:03:26,308 --> 01:03:28,575
Really don't like
to talk about it.

1110
01:03:29,860 --> 01:03:31,415
It was Quang Tri Province.

1111
01:03:32,048 --> 01:03:34,526
December 24th, 1968.

1112
01:03:36,861 --> 01:03:39,238
Dweeble was watching
the outer perimeter.

1113
01:03:40,101 --> 01:03:43,239
Jackson and Pollock
bringing C-rations.

1114
01:03:44,285 --> 01:03:47,702
Taylor was playing Canasta
through it all with Shovel Face.

1115
01:03:50,197 --> 01:03:53,048
Cong mortar shell fired
from half a mile out.

1116
01:03:53,696 --> 01:03:55,418
Landed right
in the middle of camp.

1117
01:03:56,552 --> 01:03:59,377
Never exploded.
It was a dud.

1118
01:04:00,361 --> 01:04:03,329
But it took his head off.
Clean at the neck.

1119
01:04:04,992 --> 01:04:07,562
Taylor was the first
to notice anything wrong.

1120
01:04:07,967 --> 01:04:10,868
He kept saying:
"Take a card, man."

1121
01:04:10,968 --> 01:04:12,371
"Take a card."

1122
01:04:12,471 --> 01:04:14,748
"If you don't discard,
you gotta take one."

1123
01:04:16,592 --> 01:04:19,049
He stared at Shovel Face
for a while.

1124
01:04:19,591 --> 01:04:21,658
Then he statred yelling
for a medic.

1125
01:04:22,175 --> 01:04:23,418
Like that would help, right?

1126
01:04:23,518 --> 01:04:26,874
Like he'd be able to apply
a tourniquet to his neck or something.

1127
01:04:28,383 --> 01:04:30,830
But it was all
too late anyway.

1128
01:04:30,930 --> 01:04:33,551
The V.C. were 
coming over the wire.

1129
01:04:33,651 --> 01:04:35,076
Thousands of them.

1130
01:04:36,847 --> 01:04:38,933
Dweeble hid all the claymores.

1131
01:04:39,440 --> 01:04:41,777
But they just kept coming.

1132
01:04:42,536 --> 01:04:44,361
Nobody survived.

1133
01:04:46,416 --> 01:04:47,879
Man...

1134
01:04:48,065 --> 01:04:50,581
I'm glad I was in grade school.

1135
01:04:54,007 --> 01:04:56,139
I don't think
I could have dealt with it.

1136
01:05:02,701 --> 01:05:04,080
Well.

1137
01:05:04,664 --> 01:05:06,161
I guess I'll, uh...

1138
01:05:06,565 --> 01:05:08,306
...watch some TV.

1139
01:05:16,002 --> 01:05:17,278
<i>Remember...</i>

1140
01:05:17,378 --> 01:05:20,640
<i>At Shady Lane Mortuaries,
we care.</i>

1141
01:05:20,740 --> 01:05:22,491
Well, I don't.

1142
01:05:22,591 --> 01:05:26,280
<i>I can't function anymore.
I'm tired of living a lie.</i>

1143
01:05:26,380 --> 01:05:30,386
I love watching soap operas.
I mean, how much worse can acting be?

1144
01:05:30,486 --> 01:05:32,421
I lik--I like it when, right before
they go to commercial,

1145
01:05:32,521 --> 01:05:33,820
they'll make the big face.

1146
01:05:33,920 --> 01:05:35,964
You know, the big face?
Eh?

1147
01:05:36,064 --> 01:05:38,436
You know, they'll have something,
like, Mark will walk in the door,

1148
01:05:38,536 --> 01:05:39,816
and this woman will go...

1149
01:05:39,916 --> 01:05:41,546
"Mark?!"

1150
01:05:42,028 --> 01:05:44,543
You know, the big face,
then they place the big music.

1151
01:05:44,643 --> 01:05:45,743
Then you come back
from the commercial,

1152
01:05:45,843 --> 01:05:48,084
and they have him walk in
the door again, and she goes:

1153
01:05:48,737 --> 01:05:51,834
"Mark.
How have you been?"

1154
01:05:51,934 --> 01:05:55,466
What happened to the big face?
It's like it never happened!

1155
01:05:56,933 --> 01:05:59,442
<i>You've made it
through the entire puzzle.</i>

1156
01:05:59,542 --> 01:06:02,757
<i>Now, for $10,000...</i>

1157
01:06:03,118 --> 01:06:06,061
<i>What famous boxer
coined the phrase,</i>

1158
01:06:06,161 --> 01:06:09,426
<i>- "I am the greatest"?</i>
- Oh, how lucky!

1159
01:06:09,526 --> 01:06:12,450
<i>Oh... I'm not
a very big sports fan.</i>

1160
01:06:12,550 --> 01:06:15,093
You don't have to be
a big sports fan, lady.

1161
